	Using deluser (Debian/Ubuntu systems)
	
	sudo deluser username groupname
	Example:
	sudo deluser akash devops
	This removes user akash from devops group.
	
	Using usermod
	
	sudo usermod -G group1,group2 username
	Important:
		This command replaces all secondary groups 
		You must specify all groups you want to keep 
	Example:
	
	sudo usermod -G docker,admin akash
	This removes akash from any other groups not listed.
	
	Command:
	
	sudo gpasswd -d username groupname
	
	Example:
	
	sudo gpasswd -d akash devops
	
	This will remove user akash from the devops group.
	
	
	
	
	
	
	

